        "text": "*[Bug 18304] sequence.default does not recycle nvec to length(from) or length(by)*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18304>\n\nMartin Maechler (<mailto:maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch|maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch\n\n--- Comment #5 from Martin Maechler (<mailto:maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch|maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch>) ---\nI'd like to apply a \"safe\" and gradual approach to changing the behaviour\n`sequence()` \nsuch that\n\n1. one *can* use a correctly recycling version of `sequence()` which fulfills\nthe \"age old\" documentation that it recycles its 3 arguments\n2. the default behavior for now will be 100% (well, in some sense) back\ncompatible.\n3. in the future, the default behaviour will be \"fully recycling\" but the\ncurrent (then \"old\") behaviour is still available\n\n4. Consequently it gets a new argument with a default, and I'd plan to\ngradually change the default over time (years) with each yearly R x.y.0\nversion.  \n\nCurrently, I have (not committed yet, in my code only):\n        ` recycle1st = Sys.getenv(\"R_sequence_recycle1st\", \"false\") `\n\nwith help file doc\n\n&gt; `recycle1st`: `logical` or coercible to it, indicating if `nvec` is recycled, as it has always been documented to.\n&gt;               We recommend to set this to `TRUE` explicitly, as that will become default, see _Details_.\n\nand **Details:** containing\n\n. . . . . . . . . . . . . .\nArgument `recycle1st` is new since R 4.6.0; currently, the default is `FALSE`\nunless the environment variable `R_sequence_recycle1st` is set to a true value.\n\nThis provides back compatibility with R &lt;= 4.5.z, where `from` and `by` are\nrecycled or shortened to length `length(nvec)` in case that is shorter than the\nmaximal length.\n\nThe plan is to replace the environment variable with an option (`getOption`)\ndefaulting to `TRUE` and subsequently to `TRUE` without a global option, to use\nR's usual recycling semantic for all three arguments `nvec, from, by`.\n. . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n\n\nany (constructive, if possible ..-) comments?\nMy plan is to commit this in a couple of days, as I have been using and writing\nthe code a few weeks ago already.",
